quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  29,7,"And those who believe and do righteous deeds, We shall certainly purge them of their bad deeds and shall certainly reward them for the good work that they did"
  29,8,"And We have instructed mankind to be good to one's own parents. And if the two (parents) try to make you worship besides Me anyone that you have no knowledge of, obey them not! To Me is your return, and then I shall tell you what you have been doing"
  29,9,"And those who believe and do righteous deeds, We shall certainly put them among the righteous"
  29,10,"And among the people there are some who say, \"We believe in Allah.\" Then when they get hurt in Allah's way, they treat man-inflicted persecution as Allah's punishment. And then, if help comes from your Lord, they say, \"We were indeed with you.\" Is not Allah well aware of what is going on in the minds of the worlds"
  29,11,"And Allah does certainly know those who believe, and He does certainly know the hypocrites"
  29,12,"And those who suppress the Truth say to those who believe, \"Follow our path, and we shall surely bear with your errors. And they shall bear with none of their errors! They are liars, certainly indeed"
  29,13,And surely they shall bear their burdens and bear other burdens besides their own. And surely they shall be questioned on the Day of Resurrection about things they fabricated
  29,14,"And We did send Noah to his people. And he lived among them for a thousand years, save fifty. Then the deluge overtook them, and they were wicked"